From: Andy Lutomirski <luto@kernel.org>
Date: Fri, 29 Jan 2016 11:42:59 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] x86/mm: If INVPCID is available, use it to flush global
 mappings
Patch-mainline: 4.4.108
References: CVE-2017-5754 bnc#1012382 bsc#1068032
Git-commit: d8bced79af1db6734f66b42064cc773cada2ce99

commit d8bced79af1db6734f66b42064cc773cada2ce99 upstream.

On my Skylake laptop, INVPCID function 2 (flush absolutely
everything) takes about 376ns, whereas saving flags, twiddling
CR4.PGE to flush global mappings, and restoring flags takes about
539ns.

